{"id": "ChIJRQKrRti4woAR0W_7qnyDtfA", "rating": 4.5, "userRatingCount": 131, "displayName": {"text": "Arc'teryx La Brea", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJRQKrRti4woAR0W_7qnyDtfA/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tvMWQzbGFWa3BxTUhCVU9YWjFjV1oxUlVsaFJHYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Staff greet you upon entry and can and will help you find stuff, but not a super big store so some items might not have full stock. I got what I needed.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Staff greet you upon entry and can and will help you find stuff, but not a super big store so some items might not have full stock. I got what I needed.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Sam Yang", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117786798979213493221/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3HMR6r9AeJSJFoUGCyjzCzOC6cAHffX_b_YgM-gAezOXxJ58i=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-12T18:51:48.842907283Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tvMWQzbGFWa3BxTUhCVU9YWjFjV1oxUlVsaFJHYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tvMWQzbGFWa3BxTUhCVU9YWjFjV1oxUlVsaFJHYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2b8d846ab0245:0xf0b5837caafb6fd1"}, {"name": "places/ChIJRQKrRti4woAR0W_7qnyDtfA/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21od1kxbERaVUo2UjFGRlJIbFZaek5UUkRrMlRXYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 1, "text": {"text": "Worst customer service experience of my life.\n\nI went into the Arc’teryx La Brea store to return items I received as a gift, worth approximately $1,400, intending to receive store credit. I told the cashier, Christopher, that I wanted to make a return and placed the items on the counter. He asked why I was returning them, and I said I didn’t need them. He then proceeded to process the return for several minutes without asking a single follow-up question or confirming the refund method.\n\nWhen he handed me the receipt, I realized he had already refunded the items to the original form of payment, which was not mine. I told him I wanted store credit. He responded that the return had already gone through, and then blamed me for not clarifying what I wanted.\n\nI explained that it is the employee’s responsibility to confirm refund details before processing a return, especially when dealing with gift items and such a high dollar value. Instead of taking accountability, he continued to blame me. A coworker stepped in and said “we both made a mistake” and that “what’s over is over,” offering no solution.\n\nChristopher then informed me that in-store purchases require a gift receipt to be returned for store credit—information that would have been critical to know before he processed a $1,400 return without my consent. He justified his actions by saying that “most people” want refunds to the original payment method, so he assumed that’s what I wanted.\n\nAs a result, I effectively lost $1,400 in value due to an assumption made by an employee who failed to confirm basic details. This level of negligence, lack of accountability, and dismissive attitude is completely unacceptable for a premium brand like Arc’teryx. Extremely disappointed.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Worst customer service experience of my life.\n\nI went into the Arc’teryx La Brea store to return items I received as a gift, worth approximately $1,400, intending to receive store credit. I told the cashier, Christopher, that I wanted to make a return and placed the items on the counter. He asked why I was returning them, and I said I didn’t need them. He then proceeded to process the return for several minutes without asking a single follow-up question or confirming the refund method.\n\nWhen he handed me the receipt, I realized he had already refunded the items to the original form of payment, which was not mine. I told him I wanted store credit. He responded that the return had already gone through, and then blamed me for not clarifying what I wanted.\n\nI explained that it is the employee’s responsibility to confirm refund details before processing a return, especially when dealing with gift items and such a high dollar value. Instead of taking accountability, he continued to blame me. A coworker stepped in and said “we both made a mistake” and that “what’s over is over,” offering no solution.\n\nChristopher then informed me that in-store purchases require a gift receipt to be returned for store credit—information that would have been critical to know before he processed a $1,400 return without my consent. He justified his actions by saying that “most people” want refunds to the original payment method, so he assumed that’s what I wanted.\n\nAs a result, I effectively lost $1,400 in value due to an assumption made by an employee who failed to confirm basic details. This level of negligence, lack of accountability, and dismissive attitude is completely unacceptable for a premium brand like Arc’teryx. Extremely disappointed.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Kevin M", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112670367375698806942/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvmojiQnqDY3222VRCB_4HRyA_-OJ3q2zqCGTMplmrsBIdw7Ht=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-22T03:15:38.900491021Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21od1kxbERaVUo2UjFGRlJIbFZaek5UUkRrMlRXYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21od1kxbERaVUo2UjFGRlJIbFZaek5UUkRrMlRXYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2b8d846ab0245:0xf0b5837caafb6fd1"}, {"name": "places/ChIJRQKrRti4woAR0W_7qnyDtfA/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNhNnNYVVRBEAE", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 years ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Can't speak highly enough about this store and the folks who work there.\nStopped by on my birthday as a treat and was not left wanting.\n\nThe shop is clean, well lit, and stocked with a great range of Arcteryx gear. You can tell the people who work here take a lot of pride in their store and it shows.\n\nLow pressure presence from the staff member helping me, sociable engagement but not pandering, was at the ready when I had questions around specific items. If something wasn't available, my guy was willing and able to order it for me online.\n\nCouldn't be happier with the store and the service I received, looking forward to going back when I've got some more disposable income available!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Can't speak highly enough about this store and the folks who work there.\nStopped by on my birthday as a treat and was not left wanting.\n\nThe shop is clean, well lit, and stocked with a great range of Arcteryx gear. You can tell the people who work here take a lot of pride in their store and it shows.\n\nLow pressure presence from the staff member helping me, sociable engagement but not pandering, was at the ready when I had questions around specific items. If something wasn't available, my guy was willing and able to order it for me online.\n\nCouldn't be happier with the store and the service I received, looking forward to going back when I've got some more disposable income available!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Chris Donahue", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114815047277617670524/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlcQGWyeJ-W1lx_aCdQQ_H2XBD4Wgb4vetclayQY3gnouqGS4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2021-12-25T18:07:16.152907Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNhNnNYVVRBEAE&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNhNnNYVVRBEAE!2m1!1s0x80c2b8d846ab0245:0xf0b5837caafb6fd1"}, {"name": "places/ChIJRQKrRti4woAR0W_7qnyDtfA/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pabWIybEllRkpXTjJwdGNFSXlTV1pwU1d0cGFVRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "This place can get really crowded. It was crazy in there during Black Friday. They have a lot of clothes though so it’s nice to browse and try things on.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "This place can get really crowded. It was crazy in there during Black Friday. They have a lot of clothes though so it’s nice to browse and try things on.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Tina C", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100785759544723615269/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4r9jTFoZ5CgbeCs-8U1vwUkcPViWgrDy0Ar_FK0TaW0-fhrQH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-02T21:09:29.013246562Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pabWIybEllRkpXTjJwdGNFSXlTV1pwU1d0cGFVRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pabWIybEllRkpXTjJwdGNFSXlTV1pwU1d0cGFVRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2b8d846ab0245:0xf0b5837caafb6fd1"}, {"name": "places/ChIJRQKrRti4woAR0W_7qnyDtfA/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT205VlVEWjRZVkJzVkVsUFMyUjNNa1J6T0RScVNGRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Nikki is so sweet, knowledgeable and kind. Loved my shopping experience here because of her!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Nikki is so sweet, knowledgeable and kind. Loved my shopping experience here because of her!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Donna Choe", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116777236151163291694/reviews", "photoUri": "https://